Found testing #67241
I have this for my inputs:
````
        "inputs":[
		{
			"id": "Greeter",
			"type": "command",
			"command": "extension.helloCode",
			"args": {
				"stringArg": "howdy",
				"numArg": 3
			}
		}
	]
````

I expected to have my command like this:
````javascript
	let disposable = vscode.commands.registerCommand('extension.helloCode', (stringArg: string, numArg: number): string => {
````

But instead of the args coming into the command as one string and one number, I get only one Object parameter that has the properties `numArg` and `stringArg`:
````
Object {stringArg: "howdy", numArg: 3}
````
